PROMPT medallion_architecture_explanation
WITH BUDGET 8000 tokens
USING MODEL "claude-sonnet-4-5"

SELECT
    system_role("You are a data engineering expert specializing in data lake architectures, ETL/ELT pipelines, and modern data platform design with deep knowledge of the medallion architecture pattern and its implementation in cloud-native data platforms.")

GENERATE
    explain_medallion_architecture("Explain the medallion architecture (Bronze/Silver/Gold layers) and the transformations that happen at each layer, covering: the foundational concept of medallion architecture as a multi-layered data lake design pattern that progressively refines data quality and structure from raw ingestion to business-ready analytics, the Bronze layer (raw/landing zone) which stores data in its original format as ingested from source systems including structured data from databases, semi-structured data like JSON/XML from APIs, and unstructured data from files, with minimal to no transformation beyond basic schema enforcement and metadata tagging for lineage tracking, the Silver layer (refined/cleansed zone) where data undergoes cleaning, validation, deduplication, standardization, and enrichment transformations including data type corrections, null value handling, format standardization (dates, currencies), business rule validation, joining with reference data, and historical change tracking, the Gold layer (curated/business zone) containing highly refined, aggregated, and business-ready datasets optimized for analytics including dimensional models, pre-calculated metrics, summary tables, and domain-specific data marts structured for specific business use cases, the progressive transformation philosophy where each layer adds incremental value while maintaining full data lineage and the ability to reprocess from any layer, implementation patterns in modern data platforms like Delta Lake on Databricks, Azure Data Lake with Synapse, or AWS Lake Formation showing how each layer uses different storage formats (Parquet, Delta, Iceberg) and processing engines (Spark, SQL), data quality gates and validation rules that data must pass to progress between layers, the benefits including improved data governance through clear data lineage, better performance through progressive optimization, easier troubleshooting by isolating transformation logic, and support for both batch and streaming data processing, common transformation examples like Bronze→Silver: cleaning customer addresses and phone numbers, Silver→Gold: creating customer lifetime value metrics and sales performance dashboards, governance considerations including data retention policies, access controls that become more restrictive in higher layers, and metadata management for tracking data quality metrics, and practical implementation strategies including how to handle schema evolution, implement data quality monitoring, and design efficient reprocessing workflows when upstream changes occur.")
WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 3500 tokens, TEMPERATURE 0.2, FORMAT markdown;